<item>
            <title>[LU-16064] RPC from evicted client can corrupt data</title>
                <link>https://jira.whamcloud.com/browse/LU-16064</link>
                <project id="10000" key="LU">Lustre</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;when a client gets evicted OST cancels its locks, but don&apos;t wait for its RPCs to complete. this way another client can get a conflicting lock and modify data, but then in-progress RPC from the evicted client can modify data as well. then we get a situation when the healty client holding LDLM lock has some data/state in his cache which don&apos;t match actual data stored on OST.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
                <environment></environment>
        <key id="71579">LU-16064</key>
            <summary>RPC from evicted client can corrupt data</summary>
                <type id="1" iconUrl="https://jira.whamcloud.com/secure/viewavatar?size=xsmall&amp;avatarId=11303&amp;avatarType=issuetype">Bug</type>
